rComments: I thoroughly enjoyed her course. What makes her different is that it's not your usual textbook-dense course; she takes into consideration the research aspect of the sociological field. She assigned interesting readings and has inspired me to take apply to graduate programs. She is very caring... You just have to do the work!!

Doesn't really teach, she just comes to share her research work. Cares too much about experiences, don't expect to get a good mark in papers if your life isn't exactly like the articles based on them. Standards for tests and papers are pretty much decided afterwards and instructions are vague exactly because of this. AVOID HER.
AVOID HER AT ALL COSTS. I REPEAT AVOID AND DROP. YOU WILL REGRET STAYING.

This professor is painful to listen to. Her assignment guidelines are vague, her tests are not fair, her class average for the midterm was very low. It is not a reflection on the students... but HER. I hope she realizes that. Worst professor of all my 4 years. Does not deserve to teach. Could have been a great course if it was with another prof.
Interesting course but I'd rate her as an average prof when it comes to difficulty, although some would say she's a lot more difficult than most profs.
Excellent Prof! May be boring at times but only because of the material. Overall great. would highly recommend her
terrible professor and boring class. drop it!

The class was extremely interesting and I learned a lot more from it than I thought I would. The prof is very nice and interested in her work, if you read the textbook and understand it, then you will get an A no problem.
worst prof EVER. DROP IT WHILE YOU CAN... she will bore you to death and her lecture slides are useless

Worst professor I've had out of the 25 I've had.  When she talks about papers, she stresses that they "must be fair" with proper margins, etc. However, given a double spaced 2 page single sided paper, the best mark was given to a single spaced double sided paper. When questioned about it, she said that was "an exception". Judge for yourself.

Strong bias against males, every article centres around female discrimination. If you want a good mark, just say women have been treated unfairly, thats all she wants to hear. I am not angry from a bad mark, I am angry from paying $430.21 for a bad Professor.

Hard tests, but great deliverence of information. Provides thorough notes. My beef was the reliance on so many journal articles - and theres seemed to be a trend to get either an A or a C on assignments...

A thoroughly dull and dry course. Were it not a requisite for the program, I doubt anyone would enroll in it. Sitting through Cranford's two-hour lectures, wherein she went on at great length and detail about the course material, relying heavily on her Powerpoint slides, was simply too much to bear. This prof has extremely ridiculous standards. Its either an A+ or a C. Expects memorization not just knowledge. This course is horrible to begin with but unfortunetly its a prequsite. She reads from her notes, doesnt know how to make anything interesting. Very poor class participation. However, she knows her stuff - doesnt know how to present it.

i liked her class very much.she's strict on marking but exactly knows what she does.i felt that she wants students to learn practically not just memorize or doing assignments. the course helped me alot to improve a sense of 'sociology' i loved it.

Try to avoid taking a class with this prof if you can....she stands in front of the class for two hours a week and reads directly from her lecture notes and thus class is extremely boring.  Tests are essay and short answer format and you really need to know your stuff to do well.  There are also 5 assignments which are a lot of work.
zzzzzzzzzzzzz.....awful course. The material is very boring to begin with and the lectures don't help much. If this course wasn't a program requirement it wouldn't exist; nobody would take it.
